    "body": "### Problem\n\nI18n is good, it\n - Help developers to build multi language support.\n - Help people who doesn't familiar with English get into with Neovim.\n - Allow people with translation skills to contribute to the Neovim ecosystem.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA builtin I18n mechanism that allows:\n - Create portable language pack (e.g. big table in .lua file)\n - Load language packs from a folder\n - Use multiple language pack with fallback\n - Table-like dot index/newindex syntax\n - Easily get current locale on different platform\n - Switch current locale on-the-fly\n - Get strings from other locale\n\nAs reference, here's some zh_CN localized Neovim rendering from my configuration:\n>![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/810a06e3-5048-4ffc-aa82-3895a849772a)\n>![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a19bb045-210e-460a-a384-38fd4615448e)\n>![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/35e9c95a-95c4-4e3b-9bfb-f5275cba41a6)\n>![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d4de9c02-1b83-4902-a289-97b2ec28a219)",
